TITLE: Mark Zuckerberg Testifies in FTC Case to Block Virtual-Reality Deal
SUMMARY: The commission is seeking to prevent Meta Platforms from acquiring the app maker behind virtual-reality fitness game “Supernatural.”

TITLE: EU to Probe Broadcom's $61 Billion Planned Takeover of VMware
SUMMARY: Europe’s competition regulator fears deal could limit competition for some hardware.

TITLE: Amazon Agrees to Settle EU Antitrust Cases, Avoiding Fines
SUMMARY: The online retail giant settled two antitrust cases related to allegations about its treatment of third-party sellers on its platform, ending some of the bloc’s most advanced cases targeting a U.S. tech company.

TITLE: Many Hospitals Get Big Drug Discounts. That Doesn't Mean Markdowns for Patients.
SUMMARY: Through a government program aimed at helping low-income patients, some hospitals buy medications at reduced prices. They can sell them to patients and their insurers for much more.

TITLE: Star Gymnast Simone Biles Breaks With Embattled Telehealth Provider Cerebral
SUMMARY: A contract wasn’t extended between the company and the Olympic champion, who has been open about her own mental health struggles

TITLE: Netflix's Ad Tier Was Least Popular Plan in Launch Month
SUMMARY: The streaming giant’s ad-supported plan accounted for 9% of new signups in the U.S. in November, according to subscription analytics firm Antenna.

TITLE: Delta Air Lines to Roll Out Free Wi-Fi
SUMMARY: The carrier is expected to begin offering the service as soon as early 2023, intensifying competition among airlines.

TITLE: Omnibus Bill Expands Government TikTok Ban
SUMMARY: Tough measures targeting tech companies didn’t make the year-end spending legislation, after heavy lobbying by the industry.

TITLE: Dollar Stores Lead Surge in New Retail Openings
SUMMARY: The Dollar General and Dollar Tree chains are expanding sharply across underserved smaller markets.

TITLE: 3M to Stop Making, Discontinue Use of 'Forever Chemicals'
SUMMARY: The company said it has already reduced its use of PFAS, which accumulate and take a long time to break down.

TITLE: Bank of Japan Lets a Benchmark Rate Rise
SUMMARY: The surprise decision prompted the yen, which has fallen against the dollar for much of this year, to rise sharply.

TITLE: Japan Bends to Global Forces Pushing Up Rates
SUMMARY: Bank of Japan Gov. Haruhiko Kuroda gave markets one more surprise in the form of an interest-rate increase that he said wasn’t really an increase.

TITLE: Changes to 401(k) Retirement Plans Move Ahead in Congress
SUMMARY: Congress is on the verge of passing a bill that aims to help Americans save more for retirement, including raising the age people must start withdrawing money from tax-deferred retirement accounts.

TITLE: U.S. Delays Key Step for EV Subsidy Program After Foreign Pushback
SUMMARY: The Treasury Department said details on the battery-sourcing requirements that electric vehicles must meet to qualify for new tax credits will be released in March.

TITLE: Investors, Big-Company CEOs Split on Economic Optimism, Survey Says
SUMMARY: Two-thirds of chiefs of large firms are bearish about the economy, while investors and heads of midsize firms are more optimistic.

TITLE: Elon Musk's Twitter Poll Shows Users Want Him to Step Down
SUMMARY: The poll showed that 57.5% of respondents want him to leave as head of the social-media platform, bringing it fresh uncertainty.

TITLE: Lawmakers Include Boeing 737 MAX Waiver in Spending Bill
SUMMARY: The plane maker would get a reprieve from a regulatory deadline related to safety features on two new 737 MAX models under a provision included in legislation that lawmakers unveiled Tuesday.

TITLE: Sam Bankman-Fried's Lawyers Hash Out His Transfer to U.S.
SUMMARY: The FTX founder has agreed to be extradited, with lawyers drafting documents, according to a person familiar with the matter.

TITLE: FCC Deadlock Shields Wireless Companies From Privacy Penalties
SUMMARY: Cellphone carriers facing roughly $200 million in fines are for now shielded from paying by a partisan deadlock at the FCC, according to people familiar with the matter.
